France\", \"score\": 0.9962964476101204, \"rank\": 0.003708602488137437, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"CGTN Copied Erriyon Knighton\", \"from\": 205, \"to\": 233}, {\"ngram\": \"day\", \"from\": 287, \"to\": 290}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games Paris\", \"from\": 297, \"to\": 320}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 344, \"to\": 350}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/CFP Editor's note:As athletes around the world compete in the 2024 Paris Olympics, a fierce row over anti-doping issues is intensifying among global anti-doping communities.\", \"from\": 362, \"to\": 537, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"/CFP\", \"from\": 362, \"to\": 366}, {\"ngram\": \"Editor's note\", \"from\": 367, \"to\": 380}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 384, \"to\": 392}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 400, \"to\": 409}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 421, \"to\": 444}, {\"ngram\": \"a fierce row\", \"from\": 446, \"to\": 458}, {\"ngram\": \"anti-doping issues\", \"from\": 464, \"to\": 482}, {\"ngram\": \"global anti-doping communities\", \"from\": 505, \"to\": 535}]}, {\"sentence\": \"CGTN rolls out a series of reports to show the U.S.' role in the controversy and how its dominance in international sports is harming global anti-doping rules.\", \"from\": 538, \"to\": 697, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"CGTN\", \"from\": 538, \"to\": 542}, {\"ngram\": \"a series\", \"from\": 553, \"to\": 561}, {\"ngram\": \"reports\", \"from\": 565, \"to\": 572}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.' role\", \"from\": 581, \"to\": 595}, {\"ngram\": \"the controversy\", \"from\": 599, \"to\": 614}, {\"ngram\": \"its dominance\", \"from\": 623, \"to\": 636}, {\"ngram\": \"international sports\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 660}, {\"ngram\": \"global anti-doping rules\", \"from\": 672, \"to\": 696}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cover-ups, double standards and abuse of power \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 the doping scandal surrounding American sprinter star Erriyon Knighton is rapidly evolving into a crisis of credibility for the United States Anti-Doping Agency (USADA).\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 919, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 781, \"end\": 789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1680773492456475e-13, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 804, \"end\": 820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erriyon_Knighton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Erriyon Knighton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erriyon_Knighton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erriyon_Knighton\"}, {\"begin\": 878, \"end\": 910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"United States Anti-Doping Agency\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 878, \"end\": 910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"United States Anti-Doping Agency\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 912, \"end\": 917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Cover-ups\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 708}, {\"ngram\": \"double standards\", \"from\": 710, \"to\": 726}, {\"ngram\": \"abuse\", \"from\": 731, \"to\": 736}, {\"ngram\": \"power\", \"from\": 740, \"to\": 745}, {\"ngram\": \"the doping scandal\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 768}, {\"ngram\": \"a crisis\", \"from\": 846, \"to\": 854}, {\"ngram\": \"credibility\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 869}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In March, tests by the World Anti Doping Agency (WADA) for Knighton returned positive results for a banned substance.\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 1038, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 944, \"end\": 968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Anti Doping Agency\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 980, \"end\": 988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ramsbury\", \"score\": 0.9999937468128308, \"rank\": 6.245906213280524e-06, \"text\": \"Knighton\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ramsbury\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ramsbury\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"March\", \"from\": 924, \"to\": 929}, {\"ngram\": \"tests\", \"from\": 931, \"to\": 936}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 974}, {\"ngram\": \"positive results\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1014}, {\"ngram\": \"a banned substance\", \"from\": 1019, \"to\": 1037}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, USADA avoided his suspension by attributing it to meat contamination.\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1117, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1048, \"end\": 1053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his suspension\", \"from\": 1062, \"to\": 1076}, {\"ngram\": \"contamination\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1116}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. body went as far as declaring that \\\"justice was served\\\" before WADA had even reviewed the case and before the deadline for appeal had expired.\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1269, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The U.S. body\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1131}, {\"ngram\": \"justice\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1170}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 1190, \"to\": 1194}, {\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 1213, \"to\": 1221}, {\"ngram\": \"the deadline\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1245}, {\"ngram\": \"appeal\", \"from\": 1250, \"to\": 1256}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to a Reuters report published on Wednesday, a USADA scheme has allowed U.S. athletes who had committed doping violations to compete without sanctions for years.\", \"from\": 1271, \"to\": 1441, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1286, \"end\": 1293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.5353251591441975e-17, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 1327, \"end\": 1332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wednesday\", \"from\": 1314, \"to\": 1323}, {\"ngram\": \"U.S. athletes\", \"from\": 1352, \"to\": 1365}, {\"ngram\": \"doping violations\", \"from\": 1384, \"to\": 1401}, {\"ngram\": \"sanctions\", \"from\": 1421, \"to\": 1430}, {\"ngram\": \"years\", \"from\": 1435, \"to\": 1440}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, when it came to contamination cases involving Chinese swimmers, USADA took an entirely different attitude, accusing the China Anti-Doping Agency (CHINADA) and WADA of \\\"covering up the truth\\\" and demanding sanctions against Chinese athletes in spite of repeated clarifications by WADA and an independent investigation.\", \"from\": 1443, \"to\": 1771, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1500, \"end\": 1507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9997606686213368, \"rank\": 0.00023709674707710098, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1518, \"end\": 1523, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 1677, \"end\": 1684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9997606686213368, \"rank\": 0.00023709674707710098, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"contamination cases\", \"from\": 1470, \"to\": 1489}, {\"ngram\": \"an entirely different attitude\", \"from\": 1529, \"to\": 1559}, {\"ngram\": \"the China Anti-Doping Agency\", \"from\": 1570, \"to\": 1598}, {\"ngram\": \"CHINADA\", \"from\": 1600, \"to\": 1607}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1617}, {\"ngram\": \"the truth\", \"from\": 1634, \"to\": 1643}, {\"ngram\": \"sanctions\", \"from\": 1659, \"to\": 1668}, {\"ngram\": \"spite\", \"from\": 1697, \"to\": 1702}, {\"ngram\": \"repeated clarifications\", \"from\": 1706, \"to\": 1729}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1737}, {\"ngram\": \"an independent investigation\", \"from\": 1742, \"to\": 1770}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In April, a New York Times story alleged that 23 Chinese swimmers had tested positive for the same banned substance before the delayed Tokyo Olympics in 2021 and were still permitted to compete.\", \"from\": 1773, \"to\": 1967, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1785, \"end\": 1793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999816504899, \"rank\": 1.0414768190284426e-08, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 1822, \"end\": 1829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9997606686213368, \"rank\": 0.00023709674707710098, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"April\", \"from\": 1776, \"to\": 1781}, {\"ngram\": \"the same banned substance\", \"from\": 1863, \"to\": 1888}, {\"ngram\": \"the delayed Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 1896, \"to\": 1922}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This stirred up frustration and speculation, prompting both WADA and the International Olympic Committee (IOC) to defend their decision of clearing the swimmers for competition.\", \"from\": 1968, \"to\": 2145, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2041, \"end\": 2078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"frustration\", \"from\": 1984, \"to\": 1995}, {\"ngram\": \"speculation\", \"from\": 2000, \"to\": 2011}, {\"ngram\": \"both WADA\", \"from\": 2023, \"to\": 2032}, {\"ngram\": \"their decision\", \"from\": 2089, \"to\": 2103}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimmers\", \"from\": 2116, \"to\": 2128}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 2133, \"to\": 2144}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In July, WADA released an official report from Eric Cottier, the Swiss prosecutor tasked with investigating the case.\", \"from\": 2147, \"to\": 2264, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2212, \"end\": 2217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swiss_people\", \"score\": 0.7686642025883508, \"rank\": 0.30095795776002016, \"text\": \"Swiss\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swiss_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swiss_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 2150, \"to\": 2154}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 2156, \"to\": 2160}, {\"ngram\": \"an official report\", \"from\": 2170, \"to\": 2188}, {\"ngram\": \"Eric Cottier\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2206}, {\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 2255, \"to\": 2263}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cottier concluded that there was no evidence of favoritism towards China in WADA's handling of the issue and stated that WADA made a \\\"reasonable\\\" decision by placing trust in the Chinese authorities' explanation that the swimmers had unknowingly ingested a banned heart medication, traces of which were found in the hotel kitchen where the athletes were staying.\", \"from\": 2265, \"to\": 2627, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2332, \"end\": 2337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9893795959900393, \"rank\": 0.007925588302694539, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2444, \"end\": 2451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9997606686213368, \"rank\": 0.00023709674707710098, \"tex