\"rank\": 0.003708602488137437, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Silver medalists\", \"from\": 2629, \"to\": 2645}, {\"ngram\": \"their national flag\", \"from\": 2668, \"to\": 2687}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimming medal ceremony\", \"from\": 2698, \"to\": 2725}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's 4x200m freestyle relay\", \"from\": 2732, \"to\": 2766}, {\"ngram\": \"day\", \"from\": 2776, \"to\": 2779}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games Paris\", \"from\": 2785, \"to\": 2808}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 2835, \"to\": 2841}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/CFP Meanwhile in the U.S., a House Committee on China asked the Justice Department and the FBI on May 21 to investigate the case under a federal law that allows probes into suspected doping cases even if they occurred outside the U.S., according to the Associated Press (AP).\", \"from\": 2851, \"to\": 3128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2882, \"end\": 2887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_House_Permanent_Select_Committee_on_Intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.765243081751855e-19, \"text\": \"House\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_House_Permanent_Select_Committee_on_Intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_House_Permanent_Select_Committee_on_Intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 2917, \"end\": 2935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Department_of_Justice\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1373765661575356e-16, \"text\": \"Justice Department\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Department_of_Justice\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Department_of_Justice\"}, {\"begin\": 2944, \"end\": 2947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.507394115141396e-43, \"text\": \"FBI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\"}, {\"begin\": 3124, \"end\": 3126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.680591844260074e-18, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"/CFP\", \"from\": 2851, \"to\": 2855}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 2869, \"to\": 2877}, {\"ngram\": \"China\", \"from\": 2900, \"to\": 2905}, {\"ngram\": \"May\", \"from\": 2950, \"to\": 2953}, {\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 2972, \"to\": 2980}, {\"ngram\": \"a federal law\", \"from\": 2987, \"to\": 3000}, {\"ngram\": \"probes\", \"from\": 3013, \"to\": 3019}, {\"ngram\": \"suspected doping cases\", \"from\": 3025, \"to\": 3047}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 3078, \"to\": 3086}, {\"ngram\": \"the Associated Press\", \"from\": 3101, \"to\": 3121}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The world water sports governing body, World Aquatics, then confirmed to the AP that its executive director Brent Nowicki had been subpoenaed to testify in the U.S. criminal investigation into the Chinese case opened under the Rodchenkov Anti-Doping Act, which gives U.S. officials what some analysts have called \\\"near-Orwellian powers of prosecution.\\\"\", \"from\": 3130, \"to\": 3482, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3207, \"end\": 3209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.680591844260074e-18, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}, {\"begin\": 3238, \"end\": 3243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brent_Crude\", \"score\": 0.6997867160789607, \"rank\": 0.4289754319947301, \"text\": \"Brent\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brent_Crude\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brent_Crude\"}, {\"begin\": 3244, \"end\": 3251, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ronald_Nowicki\", \"score\": 0.9998233638198949, \"rank\": 0.00017666738604064805, \"text\": \"Nowicki\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ronald_Nowicki\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ronald_Nowicki\"}, {\"begin\": 3327, \"end\": 3334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9997606686213368, \"rank\": 0.00023709674707710098, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The world water sports governing body\", \"from\": 3130, \"to\": 3167}, {\"ngram\": \"World Aquatics\", \"from\": 3169, \"to\": 3183}, {\"ngram\": \"its executive director\", \"from\": 3215, \"to\": 3237}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S. criminal investigation\", \"from\": 3286, \"to\": 3317}, {\"ngram\": \"the Rodchenkov Anti-Doping Act\", \"from\": 3353, \"to\": 3383}, {\"ngram\": \"U.S. officials\", \"from\": 3397, \"to\": 3411}, {\"ngram\": \"some analysts\", \"from\": 3417, \"to\": 3430}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"near-Orwellian powers\", \"from\": 3443, \"to\": 3465}, {\"ngram\": \"prosecution\", \"from\": 3469, \"to\": 3480}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The law is \\\"a tool for USADA to put itself above the rest of the world, perhaps even to replace WADA as the global regulator for anti-doping,\\\" said WADA President Witold Banka at a session of the IOC in Paris on July 24, two days before the opening of the 2024 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 3484, \"to\": 3759, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3507, \"end\": 3512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"te