t\", \"from\": 4391, \"to\": 4396}, {\"ngram\": \"its actual practices\", \"from\": 4413, \"to\": 4433}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It noted that doping is not uncommon among U.S. athletes.\", \"from\": 4436, \"to\": 4493, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"doping\", \"from\": 4450, \"to\": 4456}, {\"ngram\": \"U.S. athletes\", \"from\": 4479, \"to\": 4492}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Anonline pollreleased by CGTN on Friday showed that 95.57 percent of respondents believe that USADA might be covering up U.S. athletes involved in doping.\", \"from\": 4495, \"to\": 4649, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4589, \"end\": 4594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Anonline\", \"from\": 4495, \"to\": 4503}, {\"ngram\": \"CGTN\", \"from\": 4520, \"to\": 4524}, {\"ngram\": \"Friday\", \"from\": 4528, \"to\": 4534}, {\"ngram\": \"95.57 percent\", \"from\": 4547, \"to\": 4560}, {\"ngram\": \"respondents\", \"from\": 4564, \"to\": 4575}, {\"ngram\": \"U.S. athletes\", \"from\": 4616, \"to\": 4629}, {\"ngram\": \"doping\", \"from\": 4642, \"to\": 4648}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, 96.54 percent criticized it as a classic example of \\\"American double standards\\\" and 95.63 percent seriously suspect that American athletes are involved in widespread false reporting.\", \"from\": 4650, \"to\": 4843, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4714, \"end\": 4722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1680773492456475e-13, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4782, \"end\": 4790, \"title\": \"http: